<section>
<title>Quicklook plugins</title>

<para>These plugins lets you view file types, that QuickLook doesn't supports out of the box.</para>
	<segmentedlist>
	<?dbhtml list-presentation="table"?>
	<segtitle>Name</segtitle>
	<segtitle>File Types</segtitle>
	<segtitle>Purpose</segtitle>
	<seglistitem>
		<seg><ulink url="http://homepage.mac.com/xdd/software/zip/">Archive.qlgenerator</ulink></seg>
		<seg>.zip, .tar archives.</seg>
		<seg>See what files are contained within an archive, without extracting it.</seg>
	</seglistitem>
	<seglistitem>
		<seg><ulink url="http://homepage.mac.com/xdd/software/folder/">Folder.qlgenerator</ulink></seg>
		<seg>Folders</seg>
		<seg>See summary of whats inside a folder.</seg>
	</seglistitem>
    <seglistitem>
        <seg><ulink url="http://www.mothersruin.com/software/SuspiciousPackage/download.html">Suspicious Package.qlgenerator</ulink></seg>
        <seg>.pkg packages</seg>
        <seg>See before you install something if things looks ok.</seg>
    </seglistitem>
    <seglistitem>
        <seg><ulink url="http://whomwah.github.com/qlstephen/">QLStephen</ulink></seg>
        <seg>files without a file extension</seg>
        <seg>Read files such as: README, INSTALL, ChangeLog, rakefile.</seg>
    </seglistitem>
    <seglistitem>
        <seg><ulink url="http://technocrank.com/downloads/">QLTorrent</ulink></seg>
